## 9. Fix hardcoded `python3` inside `run_daily_trackers.sh`

**This bit outside the systemd/crontab paths and would have failed silently.**
The script launches ML live-trackers inside detached `screen` sessions, and
line ~81 hardcoded plain `python3` (which resolves to system Python, missing
tensorflow/xgboost) instead of the venv.

Check for it:
```bash
cd /root/paper
grep -n "python3" ml_predictor/run_daily_trackers.sh
```

Fix it:
```bash
sed -i 's|bash -c "python3 ml_predictor/live_tracker.py|bash -c "/root/paper/venv/bin/python3 ml_predictor/live_tracker.py|' ml_predictor/run_daily_trackers.sh
grep -n "python3" ml_predictor/run_daily_trackers.sh   # confirm the change
```

**Commit and push this fix** so future migrations don't need to rediscover it:
```bash
git status                                    # confirm ONLY this file is staged-worthy
git add ml_predictor/run_daily_trackers.sh
git commit -m "Fix live_tracker.py call to use venv python instead of system python3"
git push
```
(Push needs a GitHub Personal Access Token as password if not already
configured — see Step 10 below. This is a git-remote concern only; the local
fix on disk works immediately regardless of push status, since cron/systemd
read the local file, not GitHub.)

**Note:** `git status` will show a lot of noise here — old committed runtime
files (`trader.log`, some `logs/*.csv`) showing as "modified" simply because
running the bot changes them, plus untracked `__pycache__/`, `venv/`, and
(correctly) the gitignored secrets/models/data files. Only ever stage the
actual code fix, not these.

