## 10. GitHub push authentication (if needed)

GitHub no longer accepts account passwords for git operations. If `git push`
prompts for a password and you don't have a token:

1. Go to `https://github.com/settings/tokens` → **Generate new token (classic)**
2. Name it, set an expiry, check the **`repo`** scope
3. Copy the token immediately (shown once)
4. On push prompt: username = GitHub username, password = paste the token
5. Optional, to avoid re-entering it every time:
   ```bash
   git config --global credential.helper store
   ```

