## 11. Crontab

```bash
crontab -e
```

```cron
TZ=Asia/Kolkata

# Algo trading system
0 9 * * 1-5 systemctl start algo >> /root/paper/logs/cron.log 2>&1
35 15 * * 1-5 systemctl stop algo >> /root/paper/logs/cron.log 2>&1

# ML predictor
40 15 * * 1-5 cd /root/paper && ./venv/bin/python3 ml_predictor/data_fetcher.py --append >> /root/paper/logs/ml_data.log 2>&1
0 22 * * 0 cd /root/paper && ./venv/bin/python3 ml_predictor/retrain.py >> /root/paper/logs/ml_retrain.log 2>&1
0 21 1-7 * 6 cd /root/paper && ./venv/bin/python3 ml_predictor/retrain.py --full >> /root/paper/logs/ml_retrain.log 2>&1
15 9 * * 1-5 cd /root/paper && ./ml_predictor/run_daily_trackers.sh >> /root/paper/ml_predictor/data/cron.log 2>&1
```

**Every Python-invoking line uses `./venv/bin/python3`, not plain `python3`.**
Cron does not activate the venv automatically — omitting this causes
`ModuleNotFoundError` even though manual (activated-shell) test runs work fine.

Verify:
```bash
crontab -l
```

