## Things deliberately NOT copied from old VPS

| Item | Why |
|---|---|
| `token.json` | Regenerates daily via `auto_login.py` |
| `ml_predictor/models/*.pkl,*.keras,metrics.json` | Retrained from scratch (Step 7) |
| `ml_predictor/data/*.csv` | Re-fetched fresh from Kite historical API (Step 7) |
| `logs/`, `spike_trades.csv`, `trader.pid` | Daily-generated, not required for operation |
| `logs/state.json` | Scalper V7 crash-recovery file; resets each trading day anyway |

## Things that ARE new-VPS-specific and must be redone each migration

| Item | Why it doesn't come from git |
|---|---|
| `config_secrets.env` | Git-ignored secret, manual copy required |
| `/etc/systemd/system/algo.service` | OS-level config, not part of repo |
| Crontab | Per-machine, not part of repo |
| venv paths in service file, crontab, and `run_daily_trackers.sh` | Only needed if using a venv instead of system-wide pip install (recommended after the 24.04/Python 3.11 conflict seen here) |
